                                <pubPlace>М.–Л.</pubPlace>: <publisher>Наука</publisher>,
                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cyrǧ" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyrǧ</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cirǧ</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>острый</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>sharp</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cyrǧ kænyn</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>точить</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>sharpen</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cyrǧag</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>всякое острое оружие или орудие (сабля, кинжал, нож, коса, серп и пр.)</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>any sharp weapon or tool (saber, dagger, knife, scythe, reaping hook etc)</q></abv:tr></sense></re><re><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyrǧīsæn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cirǧesæn</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>время, когда берутся за острое</q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">т. е. за косы, начало сенокоса</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">i.e. scythes, it is the begining of haymaking time)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>time when one takes in hand something sharp </q></abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">т. е. за косы, начало сенокоса</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">i.e. scythes, it is the begining of haymaking time)</note></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cyrǧænqyzt</orth></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сильно перебродивший</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>over fermented</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>острый</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>spicy</q></abv:tr></sense></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>cyrǧ kard rajs</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>возьми острый нож</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>take sharp knife</q></abv:tr></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>cirǧ færætæj in æ sawʒikko sær ku rakʼwæruncæ, togæj ʒagæj æj cirǧ mexi fijbæl ku ærkænuncæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>острым топором отсекают ему чернокудрую голову (и) окровавленную насаживают ее на конец острого кола</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>they cut off his black-haired head with a sharp axe (and) the blooded (head) is put on the end of a sharp stake</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Ulinkʼæ... xuskʼsogtæj cirǧ art rakodta</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Улинк развел из сухих дров сильный („острый“) огонь</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>Ulink made an intense (“sharp”) fire of dry firewood</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 23</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>cirǧagæj cæǧdun</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>истреблять холодным оружием</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>exterminate with blade weapon</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1935 I—II 69</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>cyrǧīsæny fysym ūdonyl wyd, æmæ sæm qæwbæstæ æræmbyrd ysty</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>обязанность принимать гостей по случаю начала сенокоса лежала на них, и (весь) аул собрался у них</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>it was their duty to receive guests on the occasion of the beginning of haymaking, and (all) the aul gathered at their place</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>II 126</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Закономерно из *%itigra%i- (%it%i перед %ii%i → %iс%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> и др.). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>tərǧa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>tīrǧ</w> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 256</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>tīr</w> <gloss><q>стрела</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>tez</w> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>ttīra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*tirǧ-(trγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>tiγra-</w> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tiγri-</w> <gloss><q>стрела</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigra-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigraxauda-</w> <gloss><q>с острыми шапками</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigraxauda-</w> <gloss><q>with sharp caps</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Слово %itigra%i представляет производное от корня %itig%i- ‘острый’, наличного в осетинском <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīǧ"/> | %iteǧ%i ‘острие’, ‘выступающий угол’ и пр. q. v. С другим формантом этот корень в <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>tigma-</w> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55, 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>25, 28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It has regularly developed from *%itigra%i- (%it%i before %ii%i → %iс%i, like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_yssæʒ"/> etc.). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>tərǧa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>171</biblScope></bibl></note></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>tīrǧ</w> <gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 256</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>tīr</w> <gloss><q>arrow</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>tez</w> <gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>ttīra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>*tirǧ-(trγ-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>tiγra-</w> <gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w>tiγri-</w> <gloss><q>arrow</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigra-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigraxauda-</w> <gloss><q>с острыми шапками</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>tigraxauda-</w> <gloss><q>with sharp caps</q></gloss></mentioned> = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>cīrǧxod</w></mentioned>)</note> <gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The word %itigra%i is a derivative from the root %itig%i- ‘sharp’ which is found in Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tīǧ"/> | %iteǧ%i ‘cutting edge’, ‘salient angle’ etc. q. v. There is the same root with another formant in <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>tigma-</w> <gloss><q>sharp</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55, 79</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>25, 28</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>